comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-01T14:42:18.406Z",codex-agent,Feature created from approved targeted-refresh strategy for pm health.
  "2026-04-06T23:08:06.392Z",codex-agent,"Reopened as canonical remediation tracker under pm-o7be for current audit findings wave to avoid duplicate item creation. Scope retained from prior implementation lineage and expanded for new report deltas only. Decision rationale: duplicate-check sweep in this run found no open/in-progress item directly covering this exact delta while this closed item already contains closest historical context, linked artifacts, and verification lineage."
  "2026-04-06T23:44:18.105Z",codex-agent,"Implementation start for health-validate-signal (health slice): reduce default health vectorization detail payload by summarizing stale item arrays, add explicit opt-in flag for full stale ID lists, and update completion/contracts/Pi/test parity."
  "2026-04-06T23:50:51.940Z",codex-agent,"Implemented health verbosity refinement: default health output now summarizes stale vectorization IDs and emits counts/summary metadata, while new --verbose-stale-items opt-in returns full stale ID arrays. Also added cross-surface parity for new verbosity flags (main/help/completion/contracts/Pi/tests). Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/health-command.spec.ts tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/pi-agent-extension.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (181 passed)."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-01T14:42:18.406Z",codex-agent,Auto-refresh must remain non-fatal and deterministic when semantic runtime is unavailable.
